Document: EditorFileDialog
Path: godot/classes/class_editorfiledialog.rst
Summary: The EditorFileDialog class provides a file dialog interface for the Godot editor with file selection and filtering capabilities.

Inherits: EditorWindow < ConfirmationDialog < Window < Control < CanvasItem < Node < Object

The EditorFileDialog class is a specialized dialog window used for selecting files within the Godot editor interface. It extends the ConfirmationDialog class to provide a file selection UI with support for multiple file types through filter systems. Key features include:

- File path display and navigation
- File type filtering system
- Multiple selection support
- Dialog mode configuration (open/save)
- Customizable UI elements

The class implements the following core functionality:
- File system browsing with directory navigation
- File selection with checkbox support
- Filter system for showing/hiding file types
- Dialog result handling (success/cancel)
- Integration with the editor's file management system

Key Rule: EditorFileDialog must be used within the Godot editor context and cannot be instantiated directly in scenes.
